                        <interp inst="t18560407-450-verdict-2" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.—(<hi rend="italic">He was further charged with having been before convicted.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560407-name-216" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560407-name-216" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560407-name-216" type="surname" value="PARTKIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560407-name-216" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN PARTKIDGE</persName>
                  </hi> I produce a certificate—(<hi rend="italic">Read: "Central Criminal Court, John Brown, Convicted, April</hi>, 1849, <hi rend="italic">of stealing a handkerchief from a man unknown, having been before convicted; 
Confined eighteen months</hi>)—Fox is the person—I was one of the witnesses—he served the eighteen months, and I was in the habit of seeing him every day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>.**</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Partridge stated that he had been convicted six times, and was a regular trainer, having always two or three boys with him to teach them.</hi>)</p>
               <p>Aged 27.—<hi rend="italic">
